Dialog.text: Good morning, Morgan. I'm Dr. Bellamy.
Looks like we have some tests to run through today.
Probably not the kind of thing you're used to, I imagine. But, trust me, you're going to do fantastic.
You're going to do fantastic.
All good? Great. Let's begin.
Do you see those little boxes? Wonderful.
For this first test, I'd like you to remove the boxes from the red circle as quickly as you can.
Take your time, relax. Think it over.
No, I'm kidding. You only have five seconds.
No, I'm kidding. You only have three seconds.
Hit the red button when you're ready to start.
Wonderful. That's... you're absolutely fine. Let's move on to Room B then.
Ok, Morgan. Listen carefully. I'd like you to do your best to hide in this room.
Just go with your gut. Okay? Wonderful. Press the red button when you're ready.
Hmph. I ...

Dialog.notes: Told someting dissapointing by his staff, trying to maintain positivity.
Dialog.text: Can we reset? No? That's fine.
Sorry. Let's keep things moving, Morgan. Head into Room C. You're doing marvelous.
All right. Here we go.
For this test, please press the blue button across the room as quickly as you can, in the most natural intuitive way possible.
Without thinking. Just ... go for it.
Press the red button when you're ready.

Dialog.notes: To staff. Really irritated under the surface.
Dialog.text: I'm sorry, can someone please explain to me what's happening? Simmons?
Did you double-check?
I apologize Morgan, we're having some trouble with... the equipment.
Not your fault. You're doing fabulous, actually. One last room. Let's step into D.
Can someone get me a cup of coffee? I would appreciate it. Thank you.
Ok, Morgan. Have a seat at the table for me, please.
Wonderful job. Take a look at the screen in front of you.
I'm going to show you a series of questions. Pick the answer that makes the most sense to you.
Press start on the screen when you're ready.
Good. Looks like you've got the hang of it. Keep going.
Oh, that's heavy stuff.
Good. Next.
Almost done.
Well done, well done. We're nearly through it. For this next part, I'm going to display an image.
I want you to take a good look at it. In a moment I'm going to ask you what ... uh...

Dialog.notes: A creature grabs him before he can finish his sentence.
Dialog.text: This my coffee? It's empty.
Whenever you're ready, Morgan.
Just press the red button.
The red button starts the test.
Is it warm in here?
Dr. Yu? Morgan. We're ready.
Did you see what they had in the cafeteria this morning? Crepes.
Wow. I'm... impressed.
You know what? I'd probably do the same thing.
Not your problem, right?

Dialog.notes: Spoken softer, aside to his staff. Told someting dissapointing by his staff, trying to maintain positivity.
Dialog.text: Any... synaptic register? At all? No? That's fine.
Morgan. We can see you there.
Uh- Morgan. You won't need that.
You seem excited today. Good.
Uh... Morgan. I'll have to ask you not to block the doors, please. Thanks.

Dialog.notes: Alt line for test A results.
Dialog.text: Wonderful. That was... a result. You're absolutely fine. Let's move on to Room B then.
No, I'm kidding. You only have nine seconds.
